  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Sachin Jaiswal versus M/s Hotel Alka Raje & Other pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_2_1396_1404','2025INSC275'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SACHIN JAISWAL<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>M/S HOTEL ALKA RAJE & OTHER </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1396</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 275</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003342025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SUDHANSHU DHULIA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court was justified in holding that the Hotel constructed by the late father of the appellant on the property which he had bought in 1965, was his contribution to the firm and thus, the same was brought on to the stock of the firm and would become the as per Section 14, Partnership Act. Headnotes&dagger; Partnership Act, 1932 &ndash; s.14 &ndash; Interpretation &ndash; Late father of the appellant, if had brought the property in question to the stock of the partnership firm as his contribution to the same: Held: s.14 enables a partner<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 27-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 3269/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_2_1396_1404','2025INSC275','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a